reviewText: If you're going to make a course for an online course, then face the audience and talk to the camera. We're not here to watch the side of your head while you mumble to folks sitting in front of you. It took me 10 min to decide to un-enroll from this course. This guy may know what he's talking about, but I couldn't care less.

The voice is not even clear. The instructor is focusing on the class he is teaching and not one the online one. He is explaining sometimes on board where he is not even visible so you just kind of mix and match and try to figure out what is he teaching. I had to literally put the bluetooth speaker on my ear to listen his first 3 weeks of class.

I really loved the subject matter and the lecturer was very good, but the sound was very unbalanced and there were constant interruptions in the lectures from activities that really interrupted the flow of the learning
Audio is too low in first 3 weeks. Content is not interesting.

you need to do quite a lot of side research to be able to follow along with the course, as it's lacking to provide with comprehensive definitions. it was also not featuring enough about Blockchain, which i would have expected given the very prominent place in the course title.
Blockchain content was not clear. Overall, good content
very tough for people from non financial background
